English:
Nowadays, being able to work at a company's
EDEN branch is a huge status symbol!
Chinese:
任職於EDEN裡的分公司，
這在現代可是很重要的身分地位啊！
Korean:
EDEN 속 지사에서 일한다는 건
지금은 굉장한 경력이 되지!
German:
Die Arbeit in der EDEN-Filiale einer Firma
ist heutzutage sehr angesehen!

English:
It'd be awfully nice if my kids could also
work at a big company like Kamishiro...
Chinese:
希望我家的小孩子在長大之後，
也能進入像神代這麼大的公司裡工作。
Korean:
우리 애도 카미시로 같은 큰 회사에서
일하게 되면 좋겠는데.
German:
Wäre schön, wenn meine Kinder auch in einem großen
Unternehmen wie Kamishiro arbeiten könnten ...

English:
[k150]?
That's the company created
to research the EDEN avatar system, isn't it?
Chinese:
[k150]？　你是指曾經在EDEN的化身系統的研究上
獲得良好成果的那間公司對吧。
Korean:
[k150]? EDEN의 아바타 시스템에 대한 연구로
성과를 냈던 회사잖아.
German:
[k150]?
Das Unternehmen, das zur Forschung am
Avatar-System von EDEN gegründet wurde, richtig?

English:
I think they were bought out by some big company a
long time ago, though. They aren't around anymore.
Chinese:
我聽說它在很久之前就已經被某間大企業給收購了耶。
現在那間公司本身已經不存在了。
Korean:
한참 전에 대기업에 흡수됐다고 들었는데?
지금은 더 이상 회사 자체가 존재하지 않아.
German:
Ich glaube, die wurden vor langer Zeit von einem
großen Unternehmen aufgekauft.
Die gibt es nicht mehr.

English: You didn't have anything you wanted to ask?
Chinese: 你不是有事情想要問我嗎？
